        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="141"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                <head>141. Memorandum From the Executive Secretary of the Department of State
                        (<persName corresp="#p_TPR_1">Tarnoff</persName>) to the President’s
                    Assistant for National Security Affairs (Brzezinski)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d141fn1">Source: Carter Library, National Security Affairs, Staff
                        Material, Global Issues, Bloomfield Subject File, Box 19, Kampuchea,
                        9–10/79. No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-10-26">October 26, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Kampuchea Working Group Designation</item>
                </list>
                <p>The Department has decided to form an interagency working group in the Operations
                    Center to coordinate efforts to meet the special situation of the relief of
                    displaced persons inside Kampuchea and of Khmer refugees crossing into Thailand.
                    We have placed this group under the overall direction of <persName
                        corresp="#p_CRC_1">Dick Clark</persName> who will extend his interagency
                    responsibilities for refugees to cover this unfolding tragedy.</p>
                <p>The group is charged with the implementation of the program already approved by
                    the President which makes available $39 million for disbursement principally
                    through the international organizations of <gloss target="#t_ICRC_1"
                        >ICRC</gloss>/UNICEF, the World Food Program, and the <gloss
                        target="#t_UNHCR_1">UNHCR</gloss>. The group will also direct, largely
                    through the <gloss target="#t_AID_1">AID</gloss> Disaster Relief and Food for
                    Peace offices, government liaison with voluntary agencies in the United States,
                    Thailand and Kampuchea which require special support in organizing the
                    logistical elements of their various relief programs. The working group will
                    also have the major function of coordinating responses to congressional, press
                    and public inquiries.</p>
                <pb facs="0516" n="487" xml:id="pg_487"/>
                <p>The Deputy Secretary has directed that this group be established effective at
                    1600, October 26, 1979.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TPR_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Peter Tarnoff</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d141fn2">Seitz signed for <persName corresp="#p_TPR_1"
                                >Tarnoff</persName> above <persName corresp="#p_TPR_1"
                                >Tarnoff</persName>’s typed signature.</note>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Executive Secretary</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
